correctness.rationale: The extraction is largely incorrect, mixes two different ALD processes (IGZO and N-doped SiO2), fabricates many values, and violates multiple schema constraints. Key issues: (1) Reactants: coReactant set to O3 for IGZO, whereas the article clearly states a controlled mixture of O2 and Ar plasmas; Ar as carrier/purging gas is not specified for IGZO (only for SiO2 GI), so traceability is weak. (2) Plasma power and pressure: 100 W and 1.2 Torr are from the SiO2 PEALD GI process (250 °C), not the IGZO deposition (200 °C). Moreover, the pressure unit uses “Torr” but the schema requires MilliM_HG. (3) Dosing/purge times: 0.2 s dose, 25 s purge, 10 s co-reactant, etc., are for SiO2 GI (DIPAS/N2O plasma) and not reported for IGZO; units use SEC but the schema requires MilliSEC. (4) Growth-per-cycle/number of cycles: 0.2 nm GPC and 100 cycles are not reported; growthPerCycle must use ANGSTROM per schema (NanoM used), and the thicknessControl structure is invalid (numberofCycles and filmThickness are placed inside growthPerCycle). (5) SupercycleDesign: 1:1:1 subcycles are not given in the paper; the IGZO composition is reported as In0.68Ga0.10Zn0.22O by XRF, not as a subcycle ratio. (6) Material properties: refractive index, absorption coefficient, band gap, resistivity, carrier density, roughness, density, uniformity, conformality, etc., are not reported for the IGZO film; values appear fabricated and untraceable. (7) Film composition: elementalConcentration 33.4% is incorrect (looks like a misused mobility value); atomic ratio is attributed to XPS but composition was determined by XRF. (8) Device properties: subthreshold swing is set to 0.1 mV (orders of magnitude off from 90–130 mV/dec reported); threshold voltage 0.0 V corresponds only to the 300 W case after H2 annealing, without context; deviceStructure is wrong (reported TG-BC, not bottom-gate top-contact). (9) Schema violations: wrong units for pressure (MilliM_HG required), time (MilliSEC required), length in GPC (ANGSTROM required); invalid thicknessControl object structure; placeholders like “Not Found” contradict the requirement for factual alignment; many required fields are filled with invented values (e.g., flowRates). (10) Missing processes: The article describes two ALD processes (IGZO and N-doped SiO2 GI with detailed plasma-power variations). Only one process is extracted and it conflates parameters from both, violating the requirement to extract multiple coherent processes. Properties to correct/review: coReactant, plasmaPower/pressure (and their association with the correct process), all dosing/purge/flow parameters, thicknessControl structure and units, supercycleDesign, all material and device property values (ensure traceability), deviceStructure, and add a separate, schema-compliant process for the SiO2 GI using DIPAS/N2O plasma at 250 °C, 1.2 Torr with the reported timing sequence and plasma power conditions.

completeness.rationale: The extraction is largely incorrect and incomplete relative to both the article and the schema. Major issues: (1) Missing processes and mixing of processes: The article reports at least two distinct ALD processes—PEALD-IGZO active layer (200 °C, DADI/TMGa/DEZ, O2/Ar plasma) and PEALD N-doped SiO2 gate insulator (DIPAS, N2O plasma, 250 °C, 1.2 Torr, explicit dosing/purge/plasma times, 50 nm), plus a hybrid GI (20 nm at 150 W + 30 nm at 300 W). The extraction provides only one process and mixes GI conditions (e.g., N2O plasma 100 W, 1.2 Torr, DIPAS-like timing) into the IGZO process, violating semantic coherence and traceability. (2) Factual misalignments: Co-reactant incorrectly set to O3 (article: O2/Ar plasma for IGZO); plasmaPower 100 W assigned to IGZO although that power refers to N2O plasma for SiO2 GI; dosing/purge times (0.2 s/25 s/10 s/3 s/10 s) belong to SiO2 PEALD, not IGZO; supercycle 1:1:1 is fabricated (article gives composition In0.68:Ga0.10:Zn0.22 by XRF but no subcycle ratio); device structure set to bottom-gate top-contact instead of top-gate bottom-contact (TG-BC). (3) Schema/unit violations and placeholders: Pressure unit uses Torr instead of allowed MilliM_HG; dosing/purge times use SEC rather than required MilliSEC; flow rate unit SCM-PER-MIN is inappropriate and values are fabricated; absorptionCoefficient unit PER-CENTI-M not allowed by schema; several fields use placeholders ('Not Found'), which violates the instruction to avoid null/placeholder values. (4) Fabricated or untraceable material/device properties: Refractive index, absorption coefficient, band gap, resistivity, carrier density, uniformity, conformality, roughness (1.0 nm), film density, on/off ratio are not reported in the article; SS set to 0.1 mV contradicts 90–130 mV/dec reported; threshold voltage 0.0 V only applies after H2 anneal at 300 W GI but is reported without condition; film composition method mislabeled as XPS instead of XRF. (5) Required coverage: Multiple processes should be represented separately (IGZO, SiO2 GI at each N2O plasma power and/or the hybrid GI) with correct parameters, units, and traceable values. Corrections needed: add distinct process objects for PEALD-IGZO and PEALD-SiO2 (and hybrid GI), fix co-reactant (O2/Ar plasma for IGZO), assign correct temperatures (200 °C IGZO; 250 °C SiO2), pressure (1.2 Torr→MilliM_HG), GI dosing/purge/plasma times converted to MilliSEC (e.g., 0.2 s→200 ms, 25 s→25000 ms, 10 s→10000 ms, 3 s→3000 ms), remove placeholders, remove fabricated properties not in the article, correct device structure to TG-BC, align composition ratio to XRF (0.68:0.10:0.22), and avoid inventing supercycle counts not reported.
